Here's how to implement this in .NET MAUI Shell:

## 1. Override `OnBackButtonPressed` and add a custom toolbar item

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    public EditProductPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        Shell.SetBackButtonBehavior(this, new BackButtonBehavior
        {
            Text = "Cancel",
            Command = new Command(async () => await TryNavigateBack())
        });
    }

    // Handles hardware/OS back button (Android, etc.)
    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(async () => await TryNavigateBack());
            return true; // cancel default navigation
        }
        return base.OnBackButtonPressed();
    }

    private async Task TryNavigateBack()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!leave)
                return; // user chose to stay
        }

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

## Key points

| Concern | Mechanism |
|---------|-----------|
| Custom back button text | `Shell.SetBackButtonBehavior` with `Text = "Cancel"` |
| Intercept software back | `BackButtonBehavior.Command` |
| Intercept hardware back (Android) | Override `OnBackButtonPressed()`, return `true` to cancel |
| Confirm dialog | `DisplayAlert` — navigate only if user confirms |

## 2. Track unsaved changes

Set `_hasUnsavedChanges = true` whenever the form is modified (e.g., bind to `TextChanged` events or use a dirty-tracking property in your view model).

> **Note:** iOS swipe-back gesture isn't intercepted by `OnBackButtonPressed`. Setting `BackButtonBehavior` disables the swipe gesture automatically on Shell pages, which is the desired behavior here.
